<dl id="un1013bt"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un1" href="#un1013">UN1: </a>  <a href="../../ff/unbs/un1all.htm#un1013bt"> (NLI.3) 13(bt)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> (6) <font color="green">[or]</font> pineal gland (7) <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="un1013bt"><li>Ulysses </li><li><a href="../../ulex/k/lexk.htm#un1013bt">2021</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/k/k86.htm#un1013bt">2017</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/k/k86.htm#un1013bt">1986 (9.284)</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/k/l22k.htm#un1013bt">1922</a> </li><li><ms href="#un1013bt">MS NLI.8A-9</ms> </li><li><a name="k11d" href="../udra/u9da.htm#k11d">Usage</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/k/k11d.htm#un1013bt">Draft: 9.1</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Another type of people, however, while still attaching the sixth centre to the pituitary body, bend or slant the seventh until its vortex coincides with the atrophied <mark>organ called the pineal gland</mark>, which is by that type vivified and made into a line of communication directly with the lower mental, without apparently passing through the intermediate astral plane in the ordinary way. <small> <a name="THmay1910" href="/udra/udex.htm#thmay1910"><cite title="source">The Theosophist</cite></a> (May 1910), C.W. Leadbeater, &ldquo;FORCE-CENTRES AND THE SERPENT-FIRE&rdquo; p. 1081</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
